# Keep the Docker build context small — only trims what neither
# infra/docker/api.Dockerfile nor infra/docker/web.Dockerfile ever COPY.
# Careful with globs: apps/web/public/darktiles ships thousands of tile PNGs
# the web image needs, so image exclusions below are root-anchored, not bare.

.git/
.github/
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.venv/
**/.venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
.turbo/
.vite/
coverage/
**/dist/
.playwright-mcp/
graphify-out/
scratchpad/
tmp/
test_images/
.wrangler/
site/

# Whole apps NOT referenced by either Dockerfile's COPY — apps/ml/fusion
# alone runs tens of GB of model/training artifacts, and apps/desktop's Rust
# target/ dir is gigabytes of Tauri build output. Neither image needs them.
apps/ml/
apps/desktop/
apps/native/

# Runtime data dirs (multi-GB SQLite stores + tile cache): the repo-root one
# (WORKDIR /srv path parity) and apps/api/data/ (bare-metal dev CWD, stale
# 2.7GB) and apps/web/data/ — plus doc/report assets that never cross into
# either image. Root-anchored, NOT a bare `**/data/`: that also swallowed
# apps/api/app/data/ (airports.json/ports.json/cams.yaml), which is tracked,
# COPYed into the api image via `COPY apps/api/app ./app`, and loaded at
# runtime by app/places.py and routes/cams.py.
/data/
/apps/api/data/
/apps/web/data/
/docs/media/
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
/*.gif
/*.webp
/*.pdf
/*.docx
/*.pt
/*_b64.txt
/deep-research-report.md
